This paper is primarily focused on the communication aspect of V2V technology, which falls under the category of Networked and Distributed Systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses channel models and their impact on V2V communication, which is related to Information Theory (cs.IT). The analysis of V2V success probability can also be considered as a form of Mathematical Analysis (cs.MA). The paper's focus on improving road safety and traffic efficiency suggests that it may also fall under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses potential security risks associated with V2V communication, which is related to Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
